<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Ok so that first chapter takes place in July 2019, following the events of the rest of the chapters of the book. This is after their Junior year and b<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Ok so that first chapter takes place in July 2019, following the events of the rest of the chapters of the book. This is after their Junior year and before their Senior year. In this book I think their school starts in August and ends in June but I might be wrong. Assuming Liam has just started school as a freshman, their schooling time would have looked like this: Freshman Aug 2017- Jun 2018, Sophomore Aug 2018- Jun 2019, Junior Aug 2019- Jun 2020 etc. So in conclusion I have no idea. <br />If Liam was starting their senior year August 2019 then using my calculations their freshman year would have been August 2016-Jun 2017. Most likely a small error in identifying the year they were a freshman so in actuality the author should have said it was August 2016. But I don’t know I’ve kind of confused myself thinking about it. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
